Aggregate an imputed dataset

aggregate_impute.Rd

Aggregate an imputed dataset

aggregate_impute(object, grouping, fun, filter, join)

# S4 method for ANY
aggregate_impute(object, grouping, fun, filter, join)

# S4 method for rawImputed
aggregate_impute(object, grouping, fun, filter, join)

# S4 method for aggregatedImputed
aggregate_impute(object, grouping, fun, filter,
  join)

Arguments

object

a rawImputed object
grouping

a vector of variables names to group the aggregation on
fun

the function to aggregate
filter

an optional argument to filter the raw dataset before aggregation. Will be passed to the .dots argument of filter_
join

an optional argument to filter the raw dataset based on a data.frame. A semi_join will be applied with join or each element of join in case join is a list

Examples

dataset <- generateData(n.year = 10, n.site = 50, n.run = 1)
dataset$Count[sample(nrow(dataset), 50)] <- NA
model <- lm(Count ~ Year + factor(Period) + factor(Site), data = dataset)
imputed <- impute(data = dataset, model = model)
aggregate_impute(imputed, grouping = c("Year", "Period"), fun = sum)
